MineOS is a server front-end to ease managing Minecraft administrative tasks.
For more info, see https://github.com/hexparrot/mineos-node

DEFAULT SETTINGS:

        The Admin Portal is at http://xxx.yyy.zzz.aaa:8443/
        The user for the Admin Portal is "mcserver" with password "mcserver"
        The data directory is /var/games/minecraft

CUSTOMIZATION:

        To change the default settings, edit the configuration file
        /etc/mineos.conf and restart the mineos service

        User management is done via FreeBSD's standard tools, e.g.
        - passwd mcserver    To change the default password for user mcserver
        - adduser            To create additional users
